open with project's folder with vs code

open terminal run ngrok http 3000
open terminal change directory to words and run npm start
open terminal change directory to words-server and run npm run dev

npx expo export -p web/ npx expo serve
mkdir windows-app
cd windows-app
npm init -y
npm install electron electron-builder --save-dev
npm start
in html of exported web with remove defer from the script tag and remove / from script link on expo index.html(dist)
copy dist assets folder to C://assets
npm install -g electron-packager
npx electron-packager . MyApp --platform=win32 --arch=x64 --out=dist --overwrite
after put C:\Users\styli\OneDrive\Documents\Projects\wordie-app\windows-app\dist\MyApp-win32-x64\resources\app
